Thomas Cain's mother Ora Mae died in 1943 when he was just 12 years old . 
  He had assumed there were no surviving photographs of his mother . 
  But granddaughter Andrea Ferrell tracked down an old photograph from the 1920s . 
  She gave it to him in 2013 after finding it from a distant relative . 
  Mr Cain was shocked and cried when he saw the photograph . 
 